Usage: report_annotated_assertions [-help] <object_list> [-list_annotated]
                                   [-list_non_annotated] [-max_lines <number>]
                                   -type {load transition} [-view <viewName>]
                                   [> <fileName>] [>> <fileName>] [-min  | -max  | -min_max ]

-help                       # Prints out the command usage
<object_list>               # List of nets, pins, or ports to be reported
                            # (string, required)
-list_annotated             # Lists the detailed information for the specified
                            # assertion types (bool, optional)
-list_non_annotated         # Lists information for non-annotated assertions
                            # (bool, optional)
-max                        # Report maximum values of the specified assertion
                            # type (bool, optional)
-max_lines <number>         # Controls the number of output lines reported by
                            # -list_annotated or -list_non_annotated parameter
                            # (int, optional)
-min                        # Report minimum values of the specified assertion
                            # type (bool, optional)
-min_max                    # Report both values of the specified assertion
                            # type (bool, optional)
-type {load transition}     # Assertion type, load or transition, to be
                            # reported (enum, required)
-view <viewName>            # Reports the annotations for the specified
                            # analysis view (string, optional)
> <fileName>                # Writes the report to the specified file name
                            # (redirect_operator, optional)
>> <fileName>               # Writes the report to the specified filename
                            # (redirect_operator, optional)